{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dc1d25da-a7fe-4157-b894-c88e3736c51d","content":"No `SettingsPage.xaml` file exists in the workspace, so I'll provide the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to the root element pointing at your ViewModel. This enables the XAML compiler to verify every `{Binding}` against the type at build time.\n\n**Before (uncompiled):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             x:Class=\"MyApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**After (compiled):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"MyApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Two changes:**\n1. Added `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels\"` (adjust namespace to match yours).\n2. Added `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `<ContentPage>`.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, the XAML compiler validates bindings automatically. To ensure errors surface as **build failures**:\n\n1. **Enable XamlC** (on by default in .NET MAUI, but you can be explicit):\n   ```csharp\n   // AssemblyInfo.cs or anywhere at assembly level\n   [assembly: XamlCompilation(XamlCompilationOptions.Compile)]\n   ```\n\n2. **Misspell a property to test it** — e.g., `{Binding Themee}` will now produce a build error like:\n   ```\n   XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n   ```\n\n3. **Treat warnings as errors** (optional, in your `.csproj`):\n   ```xml\n   <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n   ```\n   This promotes any binding warnings (e.g., type mismatches) to hard errors so nothing slips through.\n\n**Tip:** If a specific binding must stay dynamic (e.g., binding to an unknown type), use `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element to opt out locally while keeping compiled bindings everywhere else.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9faaf352-f00a-40f5-bb86-d93ce0a8bbc9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty and there's no SettingsPage.xaml file. The user is asking me to help them convert a page they described conceptually. I'll provide guidance and a concrete example showing how to add compiled bindings.","outputTokens":811,"requestId":"1032:22188A:1475109:1708A85:69FD3380"},"id":"d9734181-9047-48b8-a0bd-fc4c3e19408f","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:27.461Z","parentId":"2244843c-e50d-40ce-a12d-1d8ec8ac84cf"}
